  "elapsed_s": 240.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I should have described to you when I mentioned that we managed to somehow smuggle in some food and some [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] medication, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] mostly we did it in the casket when we took the dead out.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As you know, in Orthodox cemeteries, particularly, people are buried in their shrouds without actual caskets.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we smuggled the food and medication in, in the ostensibly empty basket on the way back from the burials.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And that really was one of the main sources.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] There were a few other ways in which we could manage to obtain one thing or another, but very little.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And again, it-- in one, one respect, it was time that was against us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We never had the time to organize or to plan.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we were actually told that we were going to be deported, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] at least the Jewish Council was told.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And of course, everybody got to know it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then at one point, we were again told that we have to prepare for-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] they didn't call it deportation, of course-- evacuation, or some other Aesopian language, on a certain date, which I gathered that in our case-- and I don't know whether I was in the first or the second transport from Kisvarda-- was in, on May 29, 1944.",
      "word_count": 65
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a pretty messy affair.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The-- well, we all supposedly had to present ourselves just at the front of the, of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] People were slowly coming early in the morning with whatever the weight allowance.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
